# Change discipline

- For mini modifications, touch the fewest files possible.
- Do not perform broad refactors while fixing a small issue.
- Preserve existing architecture unless asked to propose a better one.
- Before deleting code, verify it is unused or explain the risk.
- After changes, summarize what changed, why, and which files were affected.
- Mention any follow-up manual checks, missing data, or production risks.
- If the requested change conflicts with security, accessibility, SEO, performance, or maintainability, say it clearly before coding.
